{"id": "EUVD-2023-59813", "enisaUuid": "4859b466-6787-3dff-833e-7506f09262b9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs/ntfs3: don't hold ni_lock when calling truncate_setsize()\n\nsyzbot is reporting hung task at do_user_addr_fault() [1], for there is\na silent deadlock between PG_locked bit and ni_lock lock.\n\nSince filemap_update_page() calls filemap_read_folio() after calling\nfolio_trylock() which will set PG_locked bit, ntfs_truncate() must not\ncall truncate_setsize() which will wait for PG_locked bit to be cleared\nwhen holding ni_lock lock.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:23", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-24T21:30:57", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8414983c2e649364d8af29080a0869266b31abb6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6bb6b1c6b0c31e36736b87a39dd1cbbd9d5ec22f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/73fee7e1e5ea11b51c51c46e0577a197ca3602cf", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0226635c304cfd5c9db9b78c259cb713819b057e", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53163"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53163"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "04371e75-b6af-3e2d-a751-7f361be99f1f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4342306f0f0d5ff4315a204d315c1b51b914fca5 <73fee7e1e5ea11b51c51c46e0577a197ca3602cf"}, {"id": "10c7b9e7-7f20-32f6-8c1a-6856670ea03a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4342306f0f0d5ff4315a204d315c1b51b914fca5 <6bb6b1c6b0c31e36736b87a39dd1cbbd9d5ec22f"}, {"id": "40531ace-29bc-3135-a979-47f8a92bb8d9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.19"}, {"id": "487c31a9-55a0-302f-a6ab-a2f8f40f7006", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.87"}, {"id": "ba000baa-17df-344e-b475-8119b0c20d1e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.5"}, {"id": "bda8cae2-bf2b-3a69-bbf8-b4b19db9df0d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "dad26216-71e6